        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>I led the redesign, launch, and optimization of UNCOMN’s corporate website, aligning the experience with user behavior, modern UI trends, and measurable KPIs.</p>

        <h2>Problem</h2>
        <p>The existing site had outdated design, poor mobile usability, high bounce rates, and low engagement with contact forms. It didn’t reflect the innovative nature of the brand.</p>

        <h2>Strategy</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Conducted UX audits using Hotjar and GA4</li>
          <li>Developed Figma wireframes and prototypes for user testing</li>
          <li>Rebuilt layout using Elementor Pro on WordPress with performance optimizations</li>
          <li>Integrated GA4, GTM, and consent-mode compliant cookie banner</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Process</h2>
        <p>I worked collaboratively with SMEs and stakeholders, holding weekly design feedback sessions. The launch included A/B testing on key landing pages and real-time performance monitoring.</p>

        <h2>Results</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>+42.3% increase in organic traffic</li>
          <li>-22.1% decrease in bounce rate</li>
          <li>+17.4% increase in contact form conversions</li>
          <li>84.3% internal CTR on new team bio pages</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Tools Used</h2>
        <p>Figma, WordPress (Elementor), GA4, Looker Studio, Hotjar, Mailchimp, ACF, GTM</p>

